710774f-a.title: Manhattan: 12th Avenue - 43rd Street
710774f-a.text:
Twelfth Avenue, west side, at West 43rd Street, showing
street activity outside of the pier that formerly housed
the Hamburg - American Steamship Line. The photographer
states the line consists of relief recepients awaiting
their dole for the work performed by them at 5ear Mountain
Palisade Park. This was a phase of the local experiment
under the C. W. A. It was replaced with the direct govern-
ment directed projects under the W. P. A.
August 29, 1933
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
No Reproductions
